inn1.comm: good length delivery outsuide the off stump and Gayle leaves it through to the keeper

dropped! short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line and shaping away, no real width but Gayle goes for the cut, ball clips the edge and flies high towards Dhoni but he fails to hold on to a fairly easy chance, what a let-off.
on the middle and leg stump line, Gayle fails to make contact and the ball hit him on the pad
short and wide outside the off stump, bit wide, this time Gayle makes perfect contact with the cuts shot and the ball races away to the point fence
played away towards mid-on
on the middle and off stump line, hint of swing, Gayle gets right behind the line and defends it down to mid-on, watchfully played and that ends an eventful first over

beauty to start with and Agarkar strikes first ball! good length delivery, pitched touch outside the off stump and shaping back in, Chattergoon mis-judges it and shoulders arms, ball shapes in and crashes into the stumps
left alone outside the off stump, hint of swing
another good length delivery outside the off stump, shaping away, Sarwan reads it well and leaves it through to the keeper
another probing delivery outside the off stump, Sarwan leaves it through to the keeper
testing short delivery, Sarwan comfortably ducks under it
good length delivery outside the off stump, played away towards covers - end of a successful over
on the stumps, turned away towards square leg
fuller length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Gayle stays riveted on his back-foot and clips it away through midwicket, powerful shot
under pressure Sreesanth goes short and wide outside the off stump, Gayle leans back and clatters it over the fielder at cover, four more added to the total
better line and length, turned away towards square leg
on the middle and off stump line, no room offered and Gayle nicely taps it away towards gully
high fulltoss on the stumps, looked like the ball slipped out of his hand, bit of a surprise delivery and Gayle defends it on the back-foot
good length delivery, pitched outside the off stump and shaping away, Sarwan moves back and across but offers no shot and the ball goes through to the keeper
closer to the off stump line, Sarwan shuffles across, gets close to the line and defends it down on the off side
another tight delivery, close to the off stump line and Sarwan defends it on the back-foot
wayward delivery outside the off stump
another wide, again way outside the off stump and shaping away further and he is once again pulled over for reckless bowling
good length delivery outside the off stump, better line and length, Sarwan leaves it through to the keeper
short delivery, cutting in from outside the off stump, Sarwan ducks underneath it&
driven straight to the fielder at cover
good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of swing, Gayle leaves it for the keeper
bit wide outside the off stump, slanting away from the left-hander, Gayle shoulders arms
short of a good length delivery, not wide enough to free his arms but Gayle comes down hard on it, ball clips the bottom half of the bat and rolls away towards gully

slightly fuller and on the middle and off stump line, probably the slower delivery, Gayle picks it up early, steps forward to the pitch of the delivery and lofts it down to the long-on fence, top shot
wide delivery outside the off stump, Gayle has a massive swing at it but luckly for Sreesanth and India, he makes no contact.
good length delivery, angled across the left-hander, Gayle has a close look at it and at the last moment leaves it through to the keeper

good length delivery outside the off stump, width offered and Gayle has a go at it, ball clips the outside edge and flies down to third man where Munaf Patel makes a mess of things and the ball rolls over the ropes, frivolous effort to say the least
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven straight to the fielder at point
forced away towards cover point, played off the back-foot
good length delivery, Sarwan pushes forward and drives it away well wide of the fielder at mid-off, quick single and he is off the mark
line and length delivery, Gayle gets forward and strokes it down to mid-off

short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, nothing special there, Gayle pushes forward towards the ball and drills it through the gap  between cover and point, sweetly timed and the ball just rocketed away off the meat of the bat
on the middle and leg stump line, Gayle plays down the wrong line and gets hit on the pad, appeal for lbw turned down, probably missing leg
bit of width offered, Gayle drives off the back-foot but the shot is not timed well enough and the ball rolls away off the inner half of the bat
good length delivery, Gayle gets behind the line and drives it down to mid-off
another good delivery, on the middle and off stump line, defended on the back-foot - Munaf seems to have sized up Gayle he has straightaway hit a good line and length here.
strays onto middle and leg, Gayle goes back and turns it away through square leg for a single
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended on the back-foot - so far Sarwan has been very cautious in his approach
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, ball stays low after hitting the deck, Sarwan goes for the cuts and the ball sneaks under the bat, beaten by the lack of bounce there
wayward delivery down the leg side
good length delivery outside the off stump, bit of inswing but was not close enough to trouble the batsman
drifting down the leg side, Gayle fails to make contact, ball clips the pad and rolls down to fine leg

good length delivery outside the off stump, Sarwan shuffles back and across, looking to drive it away through cover point, ball clips the outside edge and flies past the diving Raina at first slip - close call
driven off the back-foot to deep backward point, nicely opened the face of the bat to get the placement right
Agarkar drifts onto the middle and leg, Sarwan gets well inside the line and nudges it down to fine leg for an easy single
on the middle and off stump line, defended on the front-foot
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Sarwan waits for it and cuts it away towards third man for a single
good length delivery, Gayle makes room and swings hard, ball clips the bottom half of the bat and rolls down to mid-on
and he gets it right on the second attempt! good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, again Gayle backs away, makes room and pulls it past the fielder at midwicket, no stopping that
cut away well wide of the fielder at cover, there is protection in the deep
inside edge and the ball rolls down to fine leg, didn't miss the leg stump by much - 50 comes up for West Indies
slower delivery and Gayle leaves it through to the keeper
short rising delivery, close to the off stump line, Sarwan shapes up for the pull but at the last moment he changes his mind and leaves it through to the keeper
driven straight to the fielder at mid-off
good length delivery, again driven straight to the fielder at mid-off
slightly short and close to the off stump line, Sarwan leans back and slices it past the fielder at gully - easy single
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Gayle makes rooms and swings hard, a ugly looking shot - ball clips the bottom edge and races away towards fine leg
driven away towards cover, no room for a single there
full and outside the off, Gayle opens the face of the bat and runs the ball down to third-man
fullish and on the off stump, driven inside out but not past the fielder at cover
Munaf bangs one in short, Sarwan goes for the pull but can't really get hold of it as he makes sure he keeps the ball down, the ball bobs away towards square-leg
short of a length and outside the off, squeezed down to third-man , it's a no-ball as well so that's two to the total
short of a driving length and outside the off, just a bit of extra bounce and the ball wobbles slightly in the air, Gayle pokes and misses
short of a length and slipping down leg, Gayle shapes to flick, the ball goes off the pad and Dhoni dives full length and stops
short of a length once more, outside the off, Gayle slaps the ball down towards gully where the ball is tidily collected
full and on the off, just a hint of away movement, defended carefully with a straight bat
short of a length and on the off, driven on the up to Sreesanth at mid-off who has a bit of a wild throw past the keeper, he seems a bit charged up!
fullish ball outside the off, Gayle watchfully leaves it alone to the keeper
quick ball that! just outside the off, decent bounce and pace there and Gayle plays and misses, the ball goes through to Dhoni nicely
short of a good length and outside the off, played down with an angled bat
short of a driving length and on the off, Gayle is careful as Agarkar is bowling in the right places. A watchful defensive shot sends the ball back down the pitch
slightly short and outside the off, Sarwan rocks back and eases that through cover gracefully
flat and on the stumps, worked away to the on side
fuller and a touch too straight, Sarwan works this wide of mid off for a single
tossed up a touch more and Gayle plays an ambitious reverse sweep but cannot beat short third-man
more orthodox this time, a defensive prod, off the inside edge onto pad, the ball rolls away to the off side
quicker through the air, a shade outside the off stump, a hint of turn, Gayle stands tall and plays a punchy defensive shot to the off side
well flighted and on the off, driven through the on side to wide midwicket
short of a good length and outside the off, a bit of turn, steered to short third-man
full and flat, defended watchfully
slightly slower, a bit more air on this one, Gayle shapes to defend, off the outside edge past the keeper
left well alone outside the off
another dot ball, end of the first Sehwag over and it's a tidy one
tossed up and outside the off, a bit of width and a touch short, cut away through point
flat and some turn from well outside the off, cut hard through the off side for a couple
well flighted and outside the off, Gayle uses his feet and swings hard at the ball, the ball skews away off the outside edge over the infield and away they go for a couple
tossed up and outside the off, through to the keeper
flatter and outside the off, steered past gully for a single
flat and just a touch too straight, Sarwan works the ball down to fine-leg
flat and on the stumps, sweep played and missed, rapped on the pads, shout for the lbw, turned down, but that has pitched outside leg and can't be given
flat and on the off a bit of turn in to Sarwan, defended
down leg, flick played and missed, through to the keeper, wide called
squeezed to the off side but not past the infield
defended down to the leg side
full-toss on the off, eased down to long-off for a single
defended to the off side. End of the over and that will be a break for drinks. West Indies are motoring along quite nicely here.
fullish and on the off, a bit of drift in, defended with bat and pad held close together
short of a good length and on the off, worked away through the on side for a single that gives Gayle the strike with a PowerPlay on!
flat and on the pads, worked down towarsd fine-leg for a single
short and a bit of width outside the off, chopped past point
flat and on the stumps, flick played and missed, rapped on the pad, the ball goes to the on side
slightly full and on the pads, whipped through midwicket for a single to end the over
flat and on the stumps, just pushed away towards midwicket
down the pitch, defensive shot played, off the pad back down the pitch
slower, too straight though, slipping down leg, past the pads and wide called
flighted, outside the off, defended carefully
short of a length and on the stumps, whipped to midwicket, there is a fielder there though and the single is saved
tossed up more and outside the off, eased down to midwicket
tossed up a bit more and on the stumps, swept uppishly down to long-leg for a couple, Sreesanth fields
down the pitch, knocked away to the leg side
another sweep shot, this time along the  ground, it's just a single though
short of a good length and outside the off, punched hard off the back foot through cover
fullish and down leg, flick played and missed, off the pad to the keeper
short of a length, on the stumps, heave played but Gayle does not get hold of it properly
Shot! He gets hold of that alright! Gayle goes down on one knee and sweeps hard to the midwicket fence
And now the other way! Powerful reverse sweep for a boundary that takes Gayle to his half-century!

GONE! That's the big wicket. Pushed through fuller and on the off, this one does not spin as much as the last two balls, Gayle goes down on one knee and tries to smash the ball out of the ground, he misses, the off stump is flattened and Sehwag celebrates as India pick up a very vital wicket
tossed up and on the off, worked away for a single to get off the mark right away
flatter, slipping down leg, left alone, wide called
again down the leg side, a play and a miss, not called a wide. Could that have been a thin edge? Doesn't matter as Dhoni does not collect cleanly
short of a length and outside the off, eased to cover
full and flat, just outside the off, Lara comes forward and pads the ball away
tossed up and on the off, defended watchfully
flatter and on the pads, worked away through the leg side for a single
turned away through square-leg for a single to end the over
defended outside the off stump
defended back down the pitch with a straight bat
tossed up a bit more and just drifting onto the pad, whipped through the leg side
short of a good length and outside the off, Lara cuts but the ball only goes down into the pitch off the bottom edge
flatter, going down leg, the ball brushes pad on the way to the keeper
Lara defends carefully and another tidy Sehwag over comes to an end
drifting down the leg side
driven wide of the fielder at mid-on
quicker delivery, driven straight to the fielder at midwicket
defended towards point
turned away towards square leg, easy single
drifting down the leg side, Sarwan leaves it through to the keeper
drifting in from close to the off stump line, Sarwan leans forward and works it away towards square leg, easy single to end the over
slightly short and drifting down the leg side, ball clips the pad and rolls down to short fine leg, in the end they decide not to go for the tight single
again worked away towards short fine leg, this time Lara calls early and sprints across, well judged single that
on the middle and off stump line, defended leaning well forward
flatter delivery on the stumps, Lara gets a big stride in and the ball hits the pad, loud appeal for lbw turned down
forced away towards covers
fuller and close to the off stump, defended stretching well forward
fuller and on the stumps, defended watchfully
tossed up on the middle and off stump line, turning in, Sarwan leans well forward and turns it away towards mid-on, Sehwag's shy at the stumps hits Sarwan on the right-hand wrist
turning in from wide outside the leg stump, Lara goes low and sweeps it away to deep square leg, a one-handed sweep to be precise
quicker and fuller, on the middle and leg stump line and Sarwan tucks it down to fine leg for a single

outside the off stump and turning across, bit too full, Lara gets a good stride forward and drives hard, opening the face of the bat at the last moment to get the placement right and the ball races away through to the gap between cover and point, lovely shot
cut away straight to the fielder at point
quicker delivery down the leg side, ball clips the pad and runs down to short fine leg
another one on the middle and leg stump line, drifting down the leg side, Sarwan leaves it through to the keeper, rightly called a wide
eased away on the leg side
turned away just wide of the fielder at midwicket, early call and a quick single is taken
hit on the pad, Lara on the front-foot looking to defend, loud appeal for lbw turned down
defended outside the off stump, got right behind the line on this occasion
nudged away towards midwicket, fielder moves across quickly and negates the chance of a single
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, driven down to mid-on
good length delivery outside the off stump, Sarwan waits for the ball and at the last moment taps it away wide of the fielder at gully

good length delivery outside the off stump, angling across, Lara comes down the track and for a moment it looked like he would get beaten by the angle but no, Lara stretches across and hammers it past the fielder at cover, there is protection in the deep and he gets just a single for that
glided down to third man for a single
probing delivery outside the off stump and Lara leaves it through to the keeper
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Lara on the back-foot pulling, ball clips the bottom edge, clips the pad and rolls down to third man
driven into the gap between cover and point
forced away towards cover point
drifting down the leg side, Sarwan shuffles across and taps it down to fine leg
fuller length delivery on the pads, was there to be hit but Lara finds the fielder at short fine leg, missed out there on some easy runs
pitched close to the off stump line and turning across, no shot offered
quicker delivery and Lara is hit on the pad, turning across and that would have missed the off stump
pitched up on the middle and leg stump line, Sarwan ends up with an inside edge onto the pad and the ball rolls away towards short midwicket - no single there

short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line and Sreesanth gets bit of extra bounce on this occasion, Sarwan stands him and pokes at it in an attempt to run it down to third man, ball zips past the outside edge
gets it right this time, bit more width and Sarwan opens the face of the bat and runs it down to third man
left alone outside the off stump
almost, well disguised slower delivery, Lara is foxed and the outside edge is produced but the ball goes well wide of the diving keeper
steered down to third man for an easy single
driven off the back-foot to the long-on region, yet another easy single added to the total

pitched outside the off stump and turning in, Sarwan goes back and turns it away towards the vacant midwicket region, Lara calls for the second run, throw comes it at the keeper's end and Dhoni quickly whips off the bails, Lara makes it across but only just, third umpire confirms
left alone outside the off stump
turning across and Lara goes back to cut, ball rolls away off the bottom half of the bat
comes down the track and drives it past the bowler for a single
turned away towards square leg
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Lara gets forward and drives, ball clips the inner half of the bat and rolls straight back down the track
worked away off the pads to the square leg region
short of a good length delivery, cutting in from close to the off stump line, Sarwan leans back and glides it down to third man for a single
well bowled slower delivery, Lara picks it up late, ball clips the inside edge and rolls away on the leg side

Sreesanth mixing it up nicely here - good length delivery, bowled from wide of the crease and angling across the left-hander, Lara comes down the track and swings across the line but fails to make contact and the ball goes over the stumps
short ball on the middle and leg stump line, pulled away off the back-foot and the ball rolls away behind square on the leg side, not a well timed shot
swept away to deep fine leg for a single
tight delivery, watchfully played back to the bowler
slightly short and Sarwan pulls it away to deep midwicket
goes for the sweep and gets hit on the pad, appeal for lbw turned down, Lara saved by the big stride there
one handed sweep and the ball races away to fine leg
turned away to short fine leg and they scamper through for a single
short of a good length length, outside the off, squeezed down to third-man for a single
slower ball on the stumps, half a shout for the lbw as Lara jams the ball down towards third-man, was that pad first? Yes it was but it has also pitched outside leg. Good call from Bucknor
fuller and on the stumps, worked to the on side
short ball banged in, a bit of tennis-ball bounce there as the ball loops past Sarwan and goes through to the keeper. There's no pace at all in this pitch
fullish and on the stumps, slanted in to Srwan who pushes the ball away to the off side
another slower one, this ends the over, Sarwan waits nicely on the ball, which is pitched just a touch short of a length and outside the off, steered down to third-man
full and on the stumps, defended down and a quick run stolen
full and on the off stumps, defended to the off side, no chance of a run
punched to the leg side, fielded tidily and there's a throw in, Sarwan manages to get back in time at the non-striker's end
worked away for yet another single
full and on the pads, Sarwan gets across his stumps nicely and flicks down to long-leg for a brace that gives him his fifty! Sarwan is really enjoying batting against this Indian attack!
full and on the off stump, the attempted yorker, Sarwan not only manages to dig the ball out he gets it away through the off side for a single

down the pitch comes Sarwan, just when we said he was batting well, a rush of blood, Sarwan tries to give himself a bit of room and hit over cover. He misses and the ball is dead on off stump. That's an important wicket for Sreesanth who has bowled really well in his second spell after going for 25 off his first three overs
full and on the off, driven well through cover, the running is good and the batsmen come back for two as the crowd roars in appreciation of Bravo
slightly short, on the stumps, Bravo goes back and pulls beautifully, that is a beautiful shot but it won't go for four, fielded on the square-leg fence
short of a good length once more, Bravo goes back and across and deflects the ball to the leg side
just short of a length and outside the off stump, cut down towards the third-man region for a single
slower ball, it's misdirected, the ball is pushed through just a bit too wide outside the off, Lara leaves it alone, Bucknor signals the wide
short of a length and enough width outside the off for Lara to chop the ball down to third-man for a brace that ends the over
short of a length and outside the off, cut away past a diving Yuvraj Singh at point
just short of a driving length and outside the off, angling away from the left-hand batsman, left alone to the keeper
fullish and on the off, glorious off drive, the ball bounces down to long off for a single, that was all Lara flourish but for only one run
fullish and slipping well down the leg side, Bravo shapes at flicking, through to the keeper and easily called a wide
short of a length and on the stumps, angling in to Bravo, that suits him and he turns the ball to the on side for a single
short and a bit of wifth, cut well but equally well fielded by Yuvraj at point
short of a good length and enough width outside the off for Lara to rock back and cut, timing the ball past point for a single to end the over
well flighted and on the pads, Lara moves to leg a little and works the ball through the on side for a single
short of a length and just outside the off, Bravo goes back and cuts, bottom edge, the ball goes just past the stumps
down the pitch comes Lara, Harbhajan adjusts well, Lara defends carefully
SHOT! This time Lara comes down the pitch and gets right to the pitch of the ball. He tees off in fine style, dead straight back over Harbhajan's head. That is a sweet shot!
sweep played and missed, rapped on the pad
down the pitch once again, this time Harbhajan sees Lara and drops it a touch short, worked to the on side
short of a good length and just outside the off, Lara tries to dab the ball to third man but misses, past the bat to the keeper
short of a length and outside the off stump, slanted down to third-man for a single
short of a good length, on the pads, worked to the on side
fuller and on the stumps, worked to the on side, Sehwag fields well and throws the stumps down at the bowler's end, which allows an overthrow as the ball ricochets away
down the pitch and a massive heave, Lara misses that one clean and the ball bobs through to the keeper
again down the pitch, slower one, not the worst idea, but the line is all wrong, well wide outside the off stumps and the extra run is conceded
short of a good length and outside the off, Lara cuts and misses. Is there just a bit of frustration mounting for the big man in his home ground?
on the pads and quite full, Lara whips it through square-leg to take a single and retain the strike

again down the pitch, worked through the on side as Harbhajan drags the ball down a touch short, they charge through for the first run, Lara slips coming back for the second, the throw is good, Dhoni whips the bails off. This one has gone up to the third umpire and it is a tight call. OUT is the decision! That is a crucial wicket here!
worked to the off side
fullish and on the off, tapped towards point for a quick single
short of a length and on the stumps, Bravo goes back and cuts the ball away very fine, just past the keeper
short of a length and just enough width for Bravo to go back, using the crease well, and cut past point
full and quite straight, driven down to long on for a single
short of a length and just outside the off stump, left alone to the keeper
short of a good length and outside the off stump, jammed down towards point
short one banded in just outside the off, Hinds has an airy cut at that and misses, the West Indies get a run anyway as it's a no-ball
better delivery this time, fullish and outside the off, Hinds tries to launch it into the stands at midwicket but makes no contact
slower ball, just outside the off, steered down to wide third-man
full and outside the off, slanting away from Hinds who shapes to steer the ball to third-man but misses
full and quite straight, flat, worked through the leg side for a single to start the over
short of a length and outside the off, cut firmly but straight to point
flat and going down leg, dabbed away just past the keeper towards short fine-leg for a sharp single
tossed up a bit more, outside the off, big booming drive, a couple of bounces down to long off
flat and on the off, quite full too, eased down towards long-off for a single
tossed up and on the pads, Bravo flicks well through midwicket, and that ends Harbhajan's quota of 10 overs
short of a length and outside the off, cut away well past point, the running is excellent and the batsmen can come back for a second
short of a driving length and on the off, Bravo waits on the ball and punches it to the on side for a single
slower one outside the off, Hinds is fooled trying to drive, so is Dhoni and the ball bobs away
fullish and outside the off, Bravo throws his bat at that in a big drive, off a thick outside edge down to third-man
full and straight, driven towards mid-on for a single to end the over
fullish and outside the off, driven inside out through cover quite well but there's a man on the fence and it's just one run

fullish and on the pads, the ball slants into the legs, Dwayne Bravo picks this up nicely and flicks down towards long-leg, Uthappa runs in a touch too hard and fumbles a catch that should have been taken
defended down to the side of the pitch, quick single scampered as Agarkar fields
full and far outside the off stump, left well alone, wide called
that's a better ball, good reverse-swinging yorker on the stumps, Hinds digs it out for a single
low full-toss outside the off, driven hard to cover, once again a quick single stolen
low full-toss outside the off, driven down to the deep, the running is very good and the batsmen can come back for a couple
short of a good length and outside the off, chopped away past point, just the single this time
slower ball outside the off, Bravo goes for the big hit, he does not quite get hold of it, but still it has enough bat on it to beat the long-off and cover fielders
short of a length and on the pads, flick played and missed, off the pad down to the keeper
slower ball down the leg side, sweep played, the ball goes off the under edge to the keeper who fumbles and allows a run
short of a length and outside the off, driven well through cover for a single
short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line, Hinds has a wild swing at it but fails to make contact
on the stumps, stroked down to long-off for a single
fulltoss on the stumps, Bravo makes room and drives hard but hits it straight to Kaif at cover, missed out there
played down to mid-on, early call and a quick single is taken, good over so far for India
another fulltoss and Hinds to misses out, driven down to long-off and he gets just a single for it
driven straight to the fielder at point, just three runs off the over - well bowled Agarkar
good length delivery, driven down to long-on for a single
driven away towards cover, Uthappa moves across quickly but fails to collect it cleanly and the batsman steal and extra run
on the middle and leg stump line, whipped away through midwicket for a brace
close to the off stump line, Bravo makes room and strokes it away well wide of the fielder at point
full and on the stumps, punched down to mid-on for a single, this is turning out to be good over for West Indies
even better! good length delivery outside the off stump, Bravo makes room and hits it over the fielder at point, nicely opened the face of the bat at the point of impact and the placement was spot on
low fulltoss, driven away towards midwicket, quick single taken
driven away just wide of Dravid at cover who fails to collect it cleanly and the batsmen scamper through for a single
yorker, Hinds jams his bat down and the ball rolls away towards point, Yuvraj's throw at the bowler's end fails to hit the target and an extra runs is given away
fulltoss on the stump and Hinds lofts it away to deep midwicket, easy pickings
on the middle and off stump line, Hinds goes for the drive and the ball rips past the outside the edge
another fulltoss, bit slower than the previous one, Hinds swings across and gets some bat on it, ball rolls away towards deep cover - nine off the over, another good one for West Indies

Patel drags it short, ball hits the track and just loops up in the air at military pace, Hinds leans back and pulls it away to the midwicket fence, fell just short of the ropes, third umpire confirms - Patel under pressure here
pitched up and driven wide of the fielder at mid-off
pitched up on the middle and off stump line, Bravo makes room and clobbers it through extra cover for the second boundary of the over - crowd loves it
worked away through square leg, Bravo takes on the fielder in the deep and makes it across comfortably, excellent running between the wickets
fifty! driven wide of the cover fielder, runs hard and once again Barvo beats the fielder and makes it back for the second, excellent innings
yorker and Bravo digs it out, ball falls dead on the track and they scamper through for a single
cover drive, ball clips the inner half of the bat and rolls away towards midwicket
driven straight back past the bowler to long-on
and the inevitable! fulltoss, drifting down the leg side, Hinds makes room and lofts it straight down the throat of Sehwag at wide long-on, Agarkar gets one more to his name, West Indies five down
eased away on the leg side, just a single
on the middle and leg stump line, worked away through midwicket, again just a single
low fulltoss, driven away towards extra cover - that's the end of Agarkar's spell
shot! fuller length delivery, on the middle and leg stump line, Bravo makes room, gets well inside the line and thuds it over extra cover
driven down to long-on
you miss I hit, full and on the stumps, Smith plays all over it and the stumps are rearranged
good length delivery outside the off stump and Ramdin strokes it down to third man for a single, through about a second but in the end they wisely decide not to go for it
driven down to long-off, gets it wide of the fielder in the deep and Bravo makes it back for the second
full and on the stumps, Bravo yorks himself and in the end had to jam his bat down, ball rolls away on the leg side and they scamper through for a single

inn2.comm: on the stumps, defended down on the off side
turned away towards square leg

believe it or not Hinds strikes! good length delivery, pitched wide outside the off stump and moving away ever-so-slightly, Uthappa plays away from him his body, nothing more than a tentative poke, ball clips the outside edge and goes straight to Ramdin behind the stumps
fuller length delivery, driven off the back-foot and the ball rolls away towards point
punched well wide of Collymore at long-on
good length delivery, close to the off stump line and Dhoni watchfully plays it away towards short cover, end of a fantastic first over from Hinds.
starts off with a sharp bouncer on the middle and off stump line, Sehwag ducks under it - one for the over signalled
another bouncer and Sehwag avoids it well, no-ball called
short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line but Sehwag goes after it, ball zips past the outside edge
better shot, another short of a good length delivery, again close to the off stump line, this time Sehwag stands tall on the back-foot and punches it away towards cover
line and length delivery outside the off stump, no shot offered
short of a good length delivery, on the middle and off stump line, no width offered and Sehwag plays it away towards extra cover
good length delivery outside the off stump, Sehwag steps back and drives hard but fails to get it past the fielder at point, Taylor too starts off with a good over
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, defended stretching well forward
full and on the pads, hint of swing and Dhoni strokes it down to mid-on
on the middle and leg stump line, Dhoni comes down the track and jabs it away to deep backward square leg
shot! on the middle and leg stump line, bit too full, Dhoni once again comes down the track, gets to the pitch of the delivery and whips it away to the fine leg fence
driven straight to the fielder at mid-on
good length delivery, shaping away and Dhoni is beaten outside the off stump, excellent delivery to end the over
on the middle and leg stump line, Sehwag leans well forward, head over the ball and whips it away straight to the fielder placed right in front of square leg
short and wide outside the off stump, Sehwag goes after it and is beaten by the lack of bounce
short of a good length delivery, this one came in with the angle, Sehwag stands rooted on his back-foot and drives it down to mid-off

Taylor drifts onto middle and leg, again slightly short in length, Sehwag stays back and pulls it down to short fine leg for a single, not a well timed shot and the ball came off the bottom half of the bat
good length delivery, probing line and length, Dhoni pushes forward and drives it away on the off side
on the middle and leg stump line, played away towards midwicket
in the slot outside the off stump and Dhoni clatters it over the point fielder, no stopping that
drifting down the leg side, Sehwag leans forward and clips it away well wide of the fielder at short fine leg
full and on the pads, turned away to short fine leg
another pitched up delivery on the pads, Sehwag leans forward and clips it away through square leg, excellent use of the wrists
good length delivery outside the off stump and Sehwag drives it through the gap between cover and point, there is protection in the deep
left alone outside the off stump, a rare sight
driven down to long-off for a single
drifting down the leg side, Dhoni fails to make contact, ball clips the pad and rolls away well wide of the fielder at short leg
good length delivery, coming in with the angle, Sehwag pushes forward and drives it away towards point
on the middle and leg stump line, again cutting in, Sehwag picks it up late and in the end had to hurry, gets his bat down in time and squeezes it away towards square leg
quicker delivery, drifting down the leg side, Dhoni looking to whip it away through midwicket makes no contact, ball hits the him high on the pad and rolls away behind the stumps on the off side
good length delivery, coming in from outside the off stump, punched away off the back-foot and the ball rolls away towards cover
fraction short and close to the off stump line, Dhoni stands erect on the back-foot and punches it away well wide of the fielder at cover, another good over from Taylor comes to an end
good length delivery outside the off stump, a fairly harmless ball, Dhoni leans back and comes down hard on it, ball clips the inside edge and crashes into the stumps - it's that maan Hinds again!
good delivery first up, defended back-to the bowler
slower delivery, Dravid gets well forward and presents the full face of the bat, ball rolls back to the bowler

good length delivery, cutting in from outside the off stump, Dravid gets a good stride forward and gets hit on the pad, impact was well outside the line of the off stump and the appeal for lbw is turned down by umpire Taufel.
defended outside the off stump
wayward delivery outside the off stump, rightly called a wide
pushed back to the bowler and another successful over from Hinds comes to an end
shot! good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Sehwag quickly gets into a good position and clips it away through midwicket, sweetly timed and placed to perfection
better line and length, defended back to the bowler
back to middle and leg stump line, Sehwag shuffles across a bit and tucks it down to fine leg for a single
short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line, Dravid moves across a bit and defends it down on the off side

drifting down the leg side, horrible delivery to say the least, Dravid leans forward, gets well inside the line and flicks it away to the fine leg fence, had four written all over it and all Dravid had to do is get bat on ball - easy runs
much better line and length on this occasion, Dravid on the back-foot defending and the ball rolls away towards cover
forced away towards cover, not a well timed shot and the ball came off the inner half of the bat
good length delivery and Sehwag drives it away through the gap between the cover fielders, sweeper hurtles across in the deep and keeps it down to just one
way outside the off stump and Dravid leaves it through to the keeper
another wide delivery outside the off stump, Dravid needlessly goes after it and ends up with a thick inside edge and the ball races away to the fine leg fence

cracking drive! good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of away movement, Dravid quickly picks up the line and length, stretches forward to the pitch of the delivery and drills it through to the gap between mid-off and cover, copy-book style
turned away off the pads to the square leg region, bit of edge involved
driven back to the bowler
beaten outside the off stump, ball rolls away off the pad
full and on the stumps, played back to the bowler
Taylor strays onto middle and leg and Dravid whips it away through square leg, fine leg had lot of ground to cover and they comfortably makes it across for the second
punched down to mid-on
good length delivery outside the off stump, Dravid is bit early into the shot and the ball rolls away off the inner half of the bat
way down the leg side, 50 comes up for India
short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line, Dravid looking to defend it on the back-foot ends up with a thick inside edge and the ball rolls away past the leg stump
on the stumps and Sehwag works it away towards midwicket, gets it just wide of the fielder there and they steal a single
defended on the front-foot
worked away on the leg side
well bowled googly, Sehwag comes down the track and the ball goes off the outside edge, falls just short of the fielder at point
worked away off the pads and gets it wide of the fielder at mid-on
beaten outside the off stump, excellent googly to end the over

width offered outside the off stump and Sehwag instinctively goes after it, ball hits the middle of the bat and flies past the fielder at cover, was in the air for a long time but the fielder there hardly got any time to react - it is a no-ball aswell
wide,  way down the leg side - Taylor continues to struggle!
turned away off the pads to the midwicket region, easy single
good length delivery outside the off stump, Dravid leans forward and drives it wide of the fielder at cover
wayward delivery outside the off stump - another wide, 6th off the innings and the second off the over
turned away through square leg for a brace

good length delivery outside the off stump, Sehwag on the back-foot driving and the ball races away to the backward point fence, looked like a gentle push but the ball just sped away off the middle of the bat
four more! drifting down the leg side and Sehwag neatly flicks it away to fine leg, fielder in the deep fails to collect it cleanly and the ball rolls overs the ropes, end of a massive over for India
defended on the back-foot
fulltoss, driven straight to the fielder at mid-on
driven away on the off side
swept away to fine leg for a single, nicely rolled his wrists over to keep the ball down

terrible mix-up! tossed up on the pads, Sehwag takes off straight away after pushing it towards silly mid-on, Dravid was not interested in the single but Sehwag never stopped and in the end Dravid had to respond, Mohammed quickly moves across to his right and scores a direct hit at the striker's end, Dravid is just short of his crease - third umpire confirms
cut away off the back-foot to deep point, Yuvraj off the mark straightaway
short of a good length and outside the off, driven on the up superbly through cover, the timing and placement are excellent, Bravo dives desperately but can't quite pull it back
played away for a single
short of a length and outside the off, Yuvraj stands tall and times that magnificently through cover point. That is a good shot from Yuvraj!
short of a length and outside the off, left well alone to the keeper
short of a length and outside the off, pushed to cover
good length ball outside the off, eased to mid off with a straight bat
flat and on the stumps, played back down the pitch
fuller and on the off stump, a bit of flight, driven back to the bowler
tossed up and outside the off, driven to cover
just outside the off, played at and missed
driven well but straight to midwicket
thrown up outside the off, spins away, Sehwag does not pick it and goes for the big drive and misses, through to the keeper
fullish and outside the off stump, Yuvraj watches it carefully and leaves it alone to the keeper
once again back of a length and outside the off, again Yuvraj watches the ball carefully and leaves it well alone
fuller and on the off, Yuvraj drives hard, off the inside edge back onto the pad, quick single taken
short of a length and outside the off stump, steered towards third-man with an angled bat
short of a good length and outside the off, driven inside out to cover
once again it's just short of a driving length, on the stumps, worked to the on side
another confident shot from Yuvraj, this time crunching a full delivery through cover, a spirited dive from Dwayne Smith stops the boundary at the ropes
defended
worked away to the leg side
fullish, outside the off, Sehwag sees it early, plants his foot down the pitch and slams the ball over the ropes at long-off! That is a glorious hit for maximum!
short of a good length and on the off, defended towards point with an angled bat
full and on the stumps, driven down the pitch towards mid-on
on the pads and on the fuller side, Yuvraj flicks and flicks well, the ball beats the infield and runs away towards deep midwicket
This is a beauty! Short of a good length and on the stumps, Yuvraj stands tall and times it imperiously towards mid-on, a diving half stop makes little difference and the ball races away to the fence
fullish and outside the off, driven hard but not past the fielder at cover
fullish and outside the off, Sehwag has to reach for it and drive, straight to cover
short of a driving length and on the stumps, driven back down the pitch to the bowler
short of a good length and on the off, Sehwag goes for this and gets under it, lofting back over the bowler's head for a boundary
slightly fuller and on the pads, worked away towards square-leg
fullish and outside the off, slower ball, Bravo has bowled that well, but Sehwag picks it and drives through cover to the sweeper on the off-side fence
short of a length and outside the off, played down to gully with an angled bat
full-toss, on the stumps, it's a slower ball gone awry, Sehwag punches to off
good-length ball outside the off, driven to cover
short of a length and outside the off, Sehwag opens the face of the bat and runs the ball down to third-man for a single
full and outside the off, Yuvraj square-drives well, Hinds runs around on the ropes and gets a good boot in to stop that
full and on the pads, flicked through midwicket, again Yuvraj's timing is good, another couple of runs
short of a good length and outside the off, punched to cover
pushed to cover for a single
short of a good length and outside the off, no turn to speak off, eased through point for a single
full and very straight, on the legs, clipped to midwicket
once again on the pads, again Yuvraj flicks but can't beat midwicket
short of a length and on the off, defended back down the pitch
tossed up a bit more and outside the off, that lands in just the right spot, Yuvraj is forced to defend watchfully
just short of a good length and outside the off stump, punched back past the bowler for a single
short of a length and outside the off, played down to third-man with an angled bat
too full, a bit too straight, Sehwag sees it early and hammers the ball through midwicket, that was quite a club!
good-length ball outside the off, punched to cover
low full-toss outside the off, Yuvraj punches but straight to the man at cover
full and on the stumps, defended watchfully
full and down the leg side, worked away past the keeper
full and outside the off, eased through cover
short of a length and on the pads, once again worked away to the deep for a single
fuller and on the pads, whipped through midwicket
pushed through a bit quicker outside the off, Sehwag feels for it and misses

beautiful ball! tossed up, on the stumps, Yuvraj is tempted to go for the big hit, the ball pitches and comes in, beating the bat and clipping leg stump. That is a big wicket for Dave Mohammed. Yuvraj Singh certainly looked in good touch.
short of a good length and down the leg side, flick played and missed, through to the keeper
short of a good length and wide outside the off, Sehwag goes to cut but misses and the ball passes over bat to the keeper
on the pads, worked away through the on side for a single
fuller and on the off, pushed to cover
overpitched and on the pads, flicked well but straight to square-leg
slower ball to end the over, Kaif defends well
defended to midwicket
on the pads, Sehwag paddles it down to short fine leg for a single
on the middle and leg stump line, bowled from over the stumps, Kaif stretches forward and defends it down on the track
clipped away through midwicket, good shot for just a single
inside edge onto the pad
forced away through cover point, another good over for West Indies comes to an end
good length delivery outside the off stump, no movement whatsoever, Sehwag pushes forward and drives it away well wide of the fielder at cover
way down the leg side, Ramdin had to dive across full length to collect the ball, excellent take
short of a good length delivery, cutting in from outside the off stump, Kaif stands tall on the back-foot and defends it down on the leg side, presented the full face of the bat there
another one down the leg side, this is terrible bowling from Bravo
fulltoss on the stumps, another horrible delivery, Kaif picks it up early and strokes it away through midwicket, excellent placement and the fielder in the deep had no chance of cutting it off
turned away to midwicket
edged away to third-man
driven to long-on
played to point
cut away to deep point
hit on the pad trying to defend
square-driven well wide of the fielder at point
defended towards cover
driven wide of the fielder at cover
pushed towards cover, the fielder gets it, no chance of a single
again a good line and length, pushed to cover, the man comes across nicely and saves the single
stroked down to mid off
driven back past the bowler but can't beat mid-on
overpitched and on the pads, whipped down to fine-leg
good length delivery, cutting in from outside the off stump, driven straight to the fielder at cover, Kaif clearly struggling here
sharp turner, Kaif is beaten by the turn, ball clips the pad and goes past the keeper
turned away towards square leg
cut away towards point, fielder moves across quickly and negates the chance of a single
forced away well wide of the fielder at point, easy single taken
turn and bounce, Kaif is once again beaten all ends up, ball clips the pad and rolls away behind beating the keeper, impact was well outside the line off the off stump
good length delivery, driven away towards extra cover
finally Kaif finds the gap, driven wide of Lara at mid-on, quick single taken
in the slot outside the off stump and Sehwag strokes it away towards deep cover
pitched up on the middle and off stump line, Kaif leans well forward and drives it straight to the fielder at midwicket
slightly short and drifting onto middle and leg, Kaif flicks it away behind square on the leg side
pitched up on the stumps and Sehwag thuds it straight back down the track, Dravo dives across full length to his right and stops it cleanly, excellent effort
comes down the track to the pitch of the delivery and drives it away through the gap between mid-on and midwicket
down the leg side, Sehwag fails to make contact
another one drifting down the leg side, Ramdin went up for a caught behind, probably in an effort to save Gayle but it didn't work
width offered outside the off stump, Sehwag leans back and cuts it away behind point
fuller in length, Sehwag pushes forward and square-drives it to the right of the fielder at point
driven down to long-on, just a single
again cut away well wide of the fielder at point, comfortably comes back for the second
turned away towards short fine leg, easy single to end a good over for India
fulltoss, driven down to long-off

goodness me! good length delivery outside the off stump, ball stopped a bit after hitting the deck, Kaif pushes forward and drives it straight to Gayle at short cover who sallows it with ease - horrible shot to say the least
driven away towards cover
good length delivery, defended outside the off stump
another tight delivery, on the stumps and angling across, Raina gets forward and defends it back to the bowler
fuller in length and touch outside the off stump, driven hard but straight back to the bowler
bowled from round the wicket, Sehwag gets forward and drives it away towards midwicket
off the mark! pitched outside the off stump and turning away, bit fuller in length and Raina punches it down to long-off for an easy single
driven down to long-off
driven straight to the fielder cover
defended back to the bowler
turned away towards midwicket, a much better from Gayle comes to an end
cut away off the back-foot to deep point, waited on to get the placement right, good shot
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, coming in with the angle, Sehwag gets right behind the line and defends it back to the bowler
fuller in length and wide outside the off stump, driven hard but straight to the fielder at cover

good length delivery, again cutting in and this one almost sneaked through, ball clips the inner half of the bat and rolls back down the track, Taylor gets a touch on it and the ball ricochets onto the stumps but Raina had it covered
on the middle and off stump line, driven straight to the fielder at midwicket
another good length delivery, angling across, Raina once again drives hard and this time he finds the fielder at mid-off
drifting down the leg side and Sehwag gets hit on the pad
driven off the back-foot, nicely opened the face of the bat and got it past the fielder at gully
on the middle and off stump line, bowled from round the wicket, Raina pushes forward and defends it down on the leg side
slightly short and that's pulled away to deep midwicket for a single
worked away towards square leg and they scamper through for a single
quicker and fuller, on the middle and off stump line and Raina defends it straight back to the bowler, another quick over from Gayle comes to an end.
yorker outside the off stump, surprise delivery, Sehwag jams his bat down and the ball goes straight to the fielder at point
good length delivery, again close to the off stump line, driven straight back past the bowler to long-off for a single

Raina goes! too short and too wide outside the off stump, a harmless ball but Raina plays a mindless cut shot and the resultant edge goes straight to Ramdin behind the stumps, India continues to slump
defended towards point, watchfully played
good length delivery, defended down on the off side
good delivery to end the over, Agarkar watchfully defends it away towards short cover, end fo a successful over
fulltoss on the middle and leg stump line, Sehwag gets inside the line and taps it away well wide of the fielder at short fine leg, excellent placement
better legth from Gayle, Sehwag reads it well and defends it down on the off side
worked away well wide of the fielder at short fine leg
driven down to long-off for a single and Agarkar is off the mark
turning in, Sehwag stays back and nudges it away towards square leg
driven wide of Lara at cover, easy single to end the over
pitched up and angling in, driven wide of Lara at mid-on, desperate dive ends in vain
well disguised slower delivery outside the off stump and Sehwag is completely and utterly foxed, drives on the up and the ball goes straight to the big man Gayle at cover
turned away to fine leg for a single
defended outside the off stump
driven straight to the fielder at midwicket
steered away to third man for a single
on the stumps, driven straight to the fielder at midwicket
another tight delivery, driven straight to the fielder at cover
punched down to long-on, just a single
turning in from outside the off stump, Harbhajan reaches out and taps it away behind point, quick single taken
cut away straight to the fielder at point
played down to fine leg for a single
driven down to long-on for a single
slow fulltoss, driven back to the bowler
another slower delivery outside the off stump, Harbhajan has a swing at it and the ball rolls away towards thirs man, bit of edge involved
short rising delivery on the middle and off stump line, Agarkar leans back, makes room and cuts it down to third man
driven hard into the ground and the ball bounces back to the bowler
fuller length delivery outside the off stump, another well disguised slower delivery, Harbhajan has a poke at it and the ball goes past the bat
drifting down the leg side, Agarkar gets well inside the line and jabs it down to fine leg for a brace
on the pads, defended on the back-foot and the ball rolls away straight to the fielder at short fine leg
tossed up outside the off stump, driven down to wide long-off for a single
quicker delivery, defended on the front-foot with a straight bat
again quicker and fuller, on the stumps and Harbhajan is made to defend
on the middle and leg stump line, turning in, played away towards midwicket
glided down to third man and they stroll across for a single
on the middle and leg stump line, driven away through the gap between mid-on and midwicket, again just a single
driven down to long-on and yet another easy single is added to the total, 53 needed from 51 balls
quicker delivery, Harbhajan fails to make contact, ball hits the pad and rolls away on the leg side
fuller length delivery outside the off stump, driven straight to the fielder at cover
too full and bit wide outside the off stump, Harbhajan jams his bat down and forces it away through cover point
turned away behind square on the leg side
low fulltoss, driven straight back to the bowler
excellent line and turning in sharply, Harbhajan is sucked forward and the edge is produced, ball goes wide of the fielder at short third man and the batsmen scamper through for a single
defended outside the off stump
driven to long-on for a single
turned away towards midwicket, another good over from Gayle comes to an end - just three runs taken off it
full-toss delivery on the pads, Harbhajan flicks but can't beat the man at midwicket
bad ball and hammered! attempted slower ball, the length was wrong, Harbhajan spotted it and smashed the ball over midwicket for a much-needed boundary
again a slower one, this time it is quite full and on the off, driven awkwardly towards cover, no run
another Harbhajan swipe! He plonks a foot down the pitch and heaves the ball over the on side. There is a fielder there and he tries hard but can't get to the ball
overpitched and on the pads, Harbhajan waits on that well and flicks it down to deep backward square-leg for a single
fullish and just outside the off, Agarkar reaches for it and drives but can only find the fielder at point
pushed away towards point and a very hasty single scampered
flatter and on the pads, flick attempted, the ball runs away past the keeper off the pads, one more to the total
googly, from the back of the hand, Harbhajan sweeps and misses, rapped on the pad
fuller and on the pads, worked away to midwicket for a quick run
Agarkar this time sees the ball outside the off and drives well to long off for a single
flat and on the off, Harbhajan gets it away to long off for another single
Fullish and on the off, Harbhajan presents the full face of the bat and drives to the bowler who bends in his followthrough and fields
low full-toss on the off, Harbhajan carves it inside out past cover for a single
slower ball, short of a good length and outside the off, steered down to third-man for a single
full and speared into the pads, Harbhajan tries to whip to leg but misses, rapped on the pad, no chance of a run
just short of a good length, outside the off, in the slot, Harbhajan smashes that one past mid off and it races away to the fence. Invaluable boundary for India!
fullish and on the off, another slower one, Harbhajan is sensible enough to wait on this one and ease the ball through cover for a single
fullish and outside the off, Harbhajan drives hard but it's only a single to long off
Agarkar now does the sensible thing, pushing to long off for another single

GONE! Harbhajan comes down the track and loses his cool. He goes for the big one and Mohammed has just held it back a touch, it arrives slowly on Harbhajan and the swinging blade can only mis-hit the ball towards long-off. Ian Bradshaw, fielding as a substitute, comes running in and throws himself a fair way to take a good catch. That is well done!
flat and on the pads, Agarkar punches firmly to the on side and picks up a single

Munaf Patel goes for the big shot first up and comes a cropper! Dave Mohammed tosses one up and Munaf goes for the sweep, it's the googly and Munaf is playing against the turn, the ball takes the top edge and balloons up to the deep. Sewnarine Chattergoon may have been embarrassed when he picked up a first-ball duck when he batted, but he takes this catch with ease! West Indies inch closer to victory!
short of a length and on the stumps, pulled away to the leg side for a single
short of a length, on the stumps, Agarkar swivels and works the ball to the leg side, a single results, Sreesanth is on strike now
spreared in on the off stump, Sreesanth somehow keeps the ball out and runs to the other end
another yorker, Agarkar is upto it and defends stoutly
eased down to long-on for a single, there's another run
full and flat, on the pads, clipped down towards short fine-leg, Chattergoon fields and fires in a superb throw, the bails fly off but Agarkar has just made it home

GONE! All over! Slighltly short, Agarkar goes for the big pull, he makes good contact but certainly not good enough to beat the fielder in the deep! West Indies come through again, four games in a row and they take the series 4-1!
